The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms and preference-based optimization to solve multi-objective optimization problems. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, given the focus on optimization and decision-making, cs.NE and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.DS, and cs.SE.
